                                may contain errors. Please, consult the References section below for
                                more information.</note>
                            <note>fragment of another theological tract in Turkish, of similar
                                character to the وصیت‌نامهٔ برگلی Vaṣiyetnāme-yi Birgeli, chiefly
                                dealing with prayers, and translated from some Arabic sources,
                                without author's name or title. This is subdivided into three faṣls;
                                the first, on fol. 89a, is headed: فی فضائل بعض الصلوة; the second,
                                on fol. 91b: ما يقال عند الصباح وعند المساء وعند النوم على الفراش و
                                عند غيرها; in this second faṣl the copy breaks off abruptly, and the
                                third is entirely missing. No date.</note>
